body:
### Describe the bug

So, I was playing a game against the engine and was with the text Move Input setting turned on. I could do other moves fine (move pieces, like playing a knight or bishop move), but couldn't castle. I tried "00", "OO", "oo", "kg1/kg8", but nothing.

### Reproduction

1. Turn on the "text Move Input" setting on;
2. Start a game against the engine;
3. Try to move using the text notation (pgn notation);
4. Reach a position where you can castle;
5. Try to castle!

### Platform and versions

Windows 11 Pro 23H2

### Stack trace

_No response_

I would like to implement this, however I can't find any standard way of representing puzzles.

I made the lichess puzzle db with a small script to convert from the specific format used by the [lichess database](https://database.lichess.org/#puzzles) to the SQL format accepted by en croissant.

